:[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be careful when assembling reducers that are scoped to cases of enum state. If a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"scoped reducer receives a child action when its state is set to an unrelated case, it will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not be able to process the action, which is considered an application logic error and will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"emit runtime warnings."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This can happen if another reducer in the parent domain changes the child state to an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unrelated case when it handles the action ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" the scoped reducer runs. For example, a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent may receive a dismissal action from the child domain:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Reduce { state, action in","  switch action {","  case .loggedIn(.quitButtonTapped):","    state = .loggedOut(LoggedOut.State())","  \/\/ ...","  }","}","Scope(state: \\.loggedIn, action: \\.loggedIn) {","  LoggedIn()  \/\/ ⚠️ Logged-in domain can't handle `quitButtonTapped`","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the parent domain contains additional logic for switching between cases of child state,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prefer "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/ifCaseLet(_:action:then:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-7sg8d"},{"type":"text","text":", which better ensures that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child logic runs "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" any parent logic can replace child state:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}